This paper belongs to the natural language processing (NLP) field, which is covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which specifically focuses on NLP research. The second likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper uses a Siamese neural network to analyze the writing style development. The third likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as NLP is a subfield of AI. The fourth likely category is cs.ED (Education), as the paper aims to identify at-risk students and analyze general development trends among high school students. The fifth likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), as the paper may have implications for how writing is taught and assessed in high schools.
